President Jacob Zuma has been called to order by the ANC s leadership after he publicly supported Andile Lungisa as the party s chairperson in Nelson Mandela Bay the Mail &amp; Guardian reported on Friday. ANC secretary general Gwede Mantashe told the newspaper that the party s top six officials had this week decided that Lungisa should be stripped of the regional chairperson post.Mantashe said the ANC s constitution did not allow members to serve on lower structures. Lungisa also serves as a member of the ANC s provincial executive committee.Last Sunday Zuma attended the regional conference in Port Elizabeth where he threw his weight behind Lungisa s election saying that the ancestors supported his election.